{"word":"οἴκημα","slug":"οἴκημα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>οἴκημα</b></el> <el>(οἴκημα, ατος, τό,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:οἰκέω'><el>οἰκέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>any inhabited place, a dwellingplace</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, attic: <i>a chamber</i>, and in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>a house</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>special senses,<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a brothel</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>: <i>a tavern</i>, <b><a href='S:Isaeus'>Isae.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a cage</i> or <i>pen</i> for animals, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>a temple, fane, chapel</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><i>a prison</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>5. </b><i>a storeroom</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>6. </b><i>a workshop</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>7. </b><i>a story</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>tabulatum</el>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}